ade a partner in the firm in exchange for tips on possible investments as startups approach lisagor about doing videos he alerts triest to those he considers the most promising for seedstage investments one example is navdy inc a san francisco company that has media buzz for its dashboardmounted device that displays text messages and smartphone apps on the windshield and allows handsfree operation by voicelast august using lisagors promotional video navdy hit  million in orders the week it launched an online sales campaign it soon closed on a seed round of  million which included ludlow and the company is reported to be raising another round of  million earlier this month a profile in forbes said that lisagors company makes arguably the best and most soughtafter product launch videos in tech ones that youve probably seen though you might not have noticed they were all made by the same guytriest said sandwich fund has closed on its first deal for a company he declined to name because the video has not been made yet well do five to  videos in the next year he said well do it from the current fund to test the model and if it works well well raise a dedicated fund as well well get the best and earliest deal flow adam hears of deals ahead of the guys on sand hill road at better valuations said triest referring to a street in menlo park calif known for its cluster of venture capital firms triest said about a third of his second fund has been invested in  portfolio companies with much of the rest of the money reserved for followon investments in those funds and for footing the bill for upcoming sandwich fund videos he said he plans to start raising a new fund of at least  million in the next few months that will be in addition to a possible dedicated fund for video production triest a member of the crains  in their s class of  launched ludlow ventures in  as an investment vehicle for family members and prior to raising the current fund he raised money from them as needed to do dealshe has coinvested in two detroit companies with detroit venture partners â€” chalkfly an online office supply company that was recently sold and upto inc which makes calendar appsalthough based in the madison building most of ludlows investments have been elsewhere including companies based in california new york nevada nebraska ohio pennsylvania and colorado tom henderson   emailÂ protected twitter tomhenderson related linksludlow ventures to raise second vc fund of  million michigan morning newsletterget a roundup of important news that happens each day facebook twitter linkedin news this weeks issuebreaking newsdetroitmichigan newsartsentertainmentauto suppliersmanufacturingentrepreneurshipfooddrinkhealth carejobstalentnonprofitspeopleelectionsreal estatesports businesstechnology blogs  opinion keith crainron fourniermary kramerother voiceseditorials extras all extrasyear in review things to do this weekendauto showdetroit homecomingflint water crisisfood economygiving guidemackinac policy conferencemichigan stock centermichigan womens directorymost connectedwayne county jail data data centerbook of listsdirectory creative detroit awards all awardsnominate in their s under  names to know in it names to know in real estatebest managed nonprofitsbiggest dealscool places to workeureka index mostinnovative companiesfast  fastestgrowing companieshealth care heroesmichigan change makersmost influential womennewsmaker of the year events all eventscrains eventslocal eventssponsored eventssubmit your event multimedia multimediavideophoto galleries connect with crains connectguide to crains detroit businessabout crains detroit businesssubscribe to crains detroit businesscontact the crains staffcontact customer servicesubscribe to email newsletterscrains reprintsclassified advertisingcrains job connectcrain content studio detroit let us tell your storycrains detroit business privacy statementbuy a copy of crainscorrections crain content studio detroit crain conten